## The Red Sea, without the crowd.

Most boat trips out of Hurghada are the same story: a big vessel, forty strangers, a fixed route and a whistle when it's time to get back on board. The water is extraordinary — the Red Sea holds some of the clearest, most coral-rich diving on the planet — and yet the day itself somehow ends up being about everyone else's schedule. A private charter fixes all of it in one move: it's your boat, your crew, your group, and your day.

Step aboard, and the whole thing slows down to your pace. Nowhere you have to be, no one you don't know, and a horizon that's nothing but blue in every direction.

## A day paced entirely around you

You set out from the marina and the crew takes you to the reefs — living coral in water so clear the fish are visible from the deck. Anchor, and you're straight in off the boat with mask and fins, floating over one of the great underwater landscapes on earth, for as long as you like. When you've had your fill, you climb back aboard to a proper lunch served on deck, cold drinks, and the sun, before moving on to the next stretch of water — or simply staying put because no one wants to move. That's the luxury of a private boat: the day bends to your group's mood, not the other way around.

> The reef, the lunch, the sun and the silence are the same on any boat. Having them to yourselves is what turns a day trip into the day you talk about for years.

## The other half of the Egypt trip

If Luxor is the soul of ancient Egypt, the Red Sea is where you exhale afterward — and a private yacht day is the best way to spend it. It's the natural companion to a Luxor temple day: the ancient world inland one day, the bluest water on earth the next, both entirely private, both arranged door to door.

We handle the yacht, the crew, the gear, the food and the transfers. You bring your group, your swimsuits, and a day with absolutely nothing to prove. Tell us the date and how many you are, and we'll have the right boat crewed and waiting.
